Species Distribution Map for Mud Snakes, Farancia abacura

M. Richard

packages<-c("dismo","utils","readxl","ggridges","ggmap", "viridis","rasterVis","maps","mapdata","raster")
sapply(packages, require, character.only=T)
extent <- extent(-130,-70,20,60)

faab_dismo <- gbif("farancia", species = "abacura", ext = extent,
             geo = TRUE, sp = TRUE, download = TRUE,
             removeZeros = TRUE)

Mud snake (Farancia abacura) Distribution Models

Static Map of Recorded Mud Snake (Farancia abacura) Distribution

faab_xy <- as.data.frame(cbind(faab_dismo@coords[,1],faab_dismo@coords[,2]))
colnames(faab_xy) <- c("longitude","latitude")

us <- map_data("state")

ggplot(data = faab_xy, aes(x=longitude, y=latitude)) +
  geom_polygon(data = us, aes(x=long, y = lat, group = group),
               fill = "white", color="black") +
  geom_point() + xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude") +
  coord_fixed(xlim = c(-125,-68), ylim = c(25,50))+
  ggtitle("Distribution Map of Mud Snakes in the United States")

Using GBIF (Global Biodiversity Information Facility), there were 1,413 observations of Mud snakes in the Southeast United States.

Predicted Distribution Using All World Climate Variables

bioclim <- getData(name = "worldclim", res = 2.5, var = "bio")
names(bioclim) <- c("Ann Mean Temp","Mean Diurnal Range","Isothermality","Temperature Seasonality",
                           "Max Temp Warmest Mo","Min Temp Coldest Mo","Ann Temp Range","Mean Temp Wettest Qtr",
                           "Mean Temp Driest Qtr","Mean Temp Warmest Qtr","Mean Temp Coldest Qtr","Annual Precip",
                           "Precip Wettest Mo","Precip Driest Mo","Precip Seasonality","Precip Wettest Qtr",
                           "Precip Driest Qtr","Precip Warmest Qtr","Precip Coldest Qtr")

bio_extent1 <- extent(x = c(
  min(faab_xy$longitude),
  max(faab_xy$longitude),
  min(faab_xy$latitude),
  max(faab_xy$latitude)))
#all climate data 
bioclim_extent1 <- crop(x = bioclim, y = bio_extent1)
bioclim_model1 <- bioclim(x = bioclim_extent1, p = faab_xy)
presence_model1 <- dismo::predict(object = bioclim_model1, 
                                 x = bioclim_extent1, 
                                 ext = bio_extent1)

# map the model using climate data 
gplot(presence_model1) + 
  geom_raster(aes(fill=value)) +
  geom_polygon(data = us, aes(x= long, y = lat, group = group),
               fill = NA, color="black") +
  geom_point(data = faab_xy, aes(x = longitude, y = latitude), color = "black", alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_fill_gradientn(colours=c("brown","yellow","darkgreen"), "Probability") +
  coord_fixed(xlim = c(-98,-75), ylim = c(25,38)) +
  xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude") + ggtitle("Probability of Mud Snake Occurrence Base on Climate Data") + 
  theme_bw() + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + theme(legend.position = "right")+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank())

Climate variables doesnt predict mud snake distribution very well. Mud snakes are freshwater obligates and are only found in/near aquatic systems: swamps, marshes, rivers, etc. I couldnt find a dataset that had water depth, presence, etc, and knowing aquatic systems are at lower elevation, I ran a model based on elevation:

Predicted Distribution of Mud Snakes Based on Elevation

#Add the elevation layer to a raster
elev_world <- getData('worldclim', var = 'alt',  res=2.5)
elev_add <- addLayer(elev_world, elev_world)


#create a model 
bioclim_extent2 <- crop(x = elev_add, y = bio_extent1)
bioclim_model2 <- bioclim(x = bioclim_extent2, p = faab_xy)
presence_model2 <- dismo::predict(object = bioclim_model2, 
                                 x = bioclim_extent2, 
                                 ext = bio_extent1)

# map the model using elevation data 
gplot(presence_model2) + 
  geom_raster(aes(fill=value)) +
  geom_polygon(data = us, aes(x= long, y = lat, group = group),
               fill = NA, color="black") +
  geom_point(data = faab_xy, aes(x = longitude, y = latitude), color = "black", alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_fill_gradientn(colours=c("brown","yellow","darkgreen"), "Probability") +
  coord_fixed(xlim = c(-98,-75), ylim = c(25,38)) +
  xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude") + ggtitle("Probability of Mud Snake Occurrence Based on Elevation") + 
  theme_bw() + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + theme(legend.position = "right")+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
